gomodel:SYNGO_904  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper studies the distribution of NKAα1 and NKAα3 in the rat spiral ganglion and in the organ of Corti\n\nFigure 5 demonstrates membrane staining for NKAα3 directly surrounding cytoplasmatic synpasin staining at the bouton-shaped terminals of the medial olivocochlear efferents that contact the outer hair cells (Fig. 5D-I). The expression of synapsin is known to label these presynapses.\n\nDouble labeling of organs of Corti with a monoclonal anti-NKAα3 (Fig. 5A) and a polyclonal anti-prestin (Fig. 5B), a protein enriched in the cell membrane of the postsynaptic OHCs, shows the NKAα3-positive fibers traveling through the tunnel of Corti and contacting the OHCs with their bouton-shaped terminals (Fig. 5C). There is no apparent postsynaptic labelling.\n\nThese staining support a presynaptic membrane localization of the NKAα3.\n\n2/7/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Whole cochleae were dissected from rats and immediately perfused through the round window with 4% paraformaldehyde (PFA) in phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) at pH 7.4." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_904" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

